# ComfyUI-Koolook environment variables
#
# Copy this file to `.env` and fill in real paths for your machine.
# `.env` is gitignored — never commit real absolute paths to the public repo.
#
# Convention: KOLOOK_* prefix. Paths can be absolute or relative to MAIN.
# When unset, code/docs fall back to the documented portable default
# (when one exists).

# --- External forks root ----------------------------------------------------
# Where raw third-party clones live (outside MAIN). See forks/README.md.
# Default if unset: ../ComfyUI-Forks
KOLOOK_FORKS_DIR=

# --- Sibling projects -------------------------------------------------------
# Sibling projects are related repositories/folders we consult but do not
# fork or vendor. See README.md "Sibling Projects".

# ComfyUI knowledge database — sibling repository of ComfyUI references,
# workflow notes, and recipe research. Used by docs/agent skills as a
# read-only knowledge source.
# Default if unset: ../ComfyUI_knowledge___DB
KOLOOK_COMFYUI_KB_DIR=

# Personal knowledge database (Obsidian or similar) — entirely user-specific.
# Optional. Leave unset on shared/public clones; agents must treat the
# absence of this var as "no personal KB available".
# No default.
KOLOOK_PERSONAL_KB_DIR=

# --- Snapshot / preset library ----------------------------------------------
# Where the Kforge Labs snapshot library lives on disk. A "snapshot" is a
# named JSON file containing your full Kforge Labs state (curated picks +
# all workflows). Saved snapshots become the preset library you can
# Load / Save / Manage from the sidebar's top action bar.
#
# Default if unset: `<comfyui-userdata>/koolook-presets/`
#   — fine for personal use; libraries stay per-install.
# Set to point at a shared location if you want:
#   - Cross-machine personal sync: a Dropbox/iCloud/Drive folder
#   - Facility shared library: an NFS/SMB mount writable by every
#     workstation, so all of them save to + load from the same library.
#
# Note: this var differs from the rest of the KOLOOK_* prefix on purpose —
# it carries the Kforge Labs branding (the user-facing tab name) so a
# facility deployment doc can refer to it without code-name baggage.
#
# Examples:
#   macOS personal sync:    /Users/<you>/Dropbox/koolook-presets
#   Linux NFS facility:     /mnt/facility-shared/koolook-presets
#   Windows SMB facility:   Z:/facility/koolook-presets
#
# The directory is auto-created on first save (its parent must already
# exist). Read-only mounts are detected — saves fail cleanly with the
# server-side reason in a toast; loads still work.
KFORGELABS_PRESETS=

# --- Local dev sync ---------------------------------------------------------
# Path to the eventual Koolook subdirectory inside your live ComfyUI
# `custom_nodes/` folder, where `scripts/sync_to_dev.py` copies runtime
# files for fast local iteration (skip the publish-and-update round-trip
# for one-line fixes). Point at the leaf, NOT the parent — the parent
# `custom_nodes/` must already exist; the script can create the leaf
# itself with `--init` on first run. Leave unset to disable; the script
# errors out cleanly if invoked without it. Forward slashes work on
# Windows too. No default — entirely user-specific.
#
# IMPORTANT: target `custom_nodes/koolook/`, NOT `custom_nodes/ComfyUI-Koolook/`.
# The ComfyUI Manager / Registry install creates `koolook/` (derived from
# `[project].name` in our pyproject.toml). Pointing dev-sync at the same
# leaf overwrites the Manager install in place — that's what you want.
# Targeting `ComfyUI-Koolook/` instead creates a second parallel install,
# and ComfyUI loads BOTH on every boot — the `__init__.py` duplicate-install
# guard will print a critical log naming both paths and disable the
# non-winning copy, but the cleanest path is to never create the dual
# install in the first place. See issue #162 for the full failure mode.
#
# Examples:
#   macOS:   /Volumes/Data/ComfyUI/custom_nodes/koolook
#   Linux:   /home/<user>/ComfyUI/custom_nodes/koolook
#   Windows: C:/ComfyUI_portable/ComfyUI/custom_nodes/koolook
#
# First-run on a fresh machine:
#   1. Set the variable here.
#   2. `python scripts/sync_to_dev.py --init` (creates the leaf folder)
#   3. From then on, plain `python scripts/sync_to_dev.py` is enough.
KOLOOK_COMFYUI_DEV_PATH=

# --- Automations working folder ---------------------------------------------
# Per-project "everything in one place" folder used by the AI-assisted
# iteration loop under `automations/`. Holds: the workflow JSON exported
# from ComfyUI, the rendered video, the generated `card.png`, and
# `iterations.md` (append-only log). One folder = one project.
#
# See `automations/CONVENTIONS.md` for the full contract.
#
# Read by:
#   - automations/scripts/make_card.py (fallback when the workflow JSON
#     has no `Working_Folder_PATH` Text Multiline node).
#   - the `/make-card` skill (.claude/skills/make-card/SKILL.md) to find
#     the newest workflow JSON to render a card for.
#
# Update this when switching projects. Forward slashes work on Windows.
# No default — leaving it unset disables the `/make-card` skill's
# auto-discovery; you can still call `make_card.py <wf.json>` directly
# and the script will use the JSON's parent directory.
#
# Examples:
#   macOS:   /Volumes/Data/JOBS/<client>/<scene>/ComfyUI-working-folder
#   Linux:   /home/<user>/JOBS/<client>/<scene>/ComfyUI-working-folder
#   Windows: N:/JOBS/<client>/<scene>/ComfyUI-working-folder
KOLOOK_AUTOMATIONS_WORK_DIR=

# Optional: override the ComfyUI log path used by `make_card.py` to extract
# render durations. By default the script infers the log location from
# KOLOOK_COMFYUI_DEV_PATH (assumes <comfyui-root>/user/comfyui.log). Set this
# only if your install writes logs elsewhere.
KOLOOK_COMFYUI_LOG=
